You can convert the strings to bytes in the EBCDIC Charset.

Note that byte has a range of -128 to 127.  Characters higher than 127 will be negative so they don&#39;t compare properly to the positive bytes. To handle that convert the EBCDIC bytes back to Strings in the default Charset and then compare them.

